---
import ServicePage from '../../components/ServicePage.astro';
---
<ServicePage
  title="Post-Renovation Cleaning in Hume City — Builders Clean Services"
  description="Professional post-renovation and builders clean in Craigieburn, Broadmeadows & Hume City. Dust, debris, and construction residue removed. Free quotes."
  heading="Post-Renovation Cleaning"
  intro="Just finished a renovation or build? Our builders' clean removes all the dust, debris, and construction residue so you can enjoy your new space straight away."
  serviceSlug="post-renovation"
  image="/images/construction-cleaning.jpg"
  features={[
    'Fine dust removal from all surfaces, walls, and ceilings',
    'Window and glass cleaning — paint splatter and adhesive removal',
    'Floor cleaning — tiles, timber, carpet vacuuming',
    'Kitchen and bathroom fit-out cleaning',
    'Cupboard and wardrobe interior wipe-down',
    'Light fitting and fan cleaning',
    'Construction debris and packaging removal',
    'Final detail clean and polish',
  ]}
  faq={[
    { q: 'When should I book a post-renovation clean?', a: 'Book as soon as you know your completion date. We recommend scheduling for the day after the final tradesperson finishes to allow dust to settle.' },
    { q: 'Do you remove construction rubbish?', a: 'We remove general construction debris and packaging. For large skip-bin loads, we recommend arranging separate waste removal.' },
    { q: 'How long does a builders clean take?', a: 'It depends on the scope of the renovation. A single room reno might take 2–3 hours; a full house renovation could take a full day. We\'ll provide an estimate with your quote.' },
  ]}
>
  <div>
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary mb-4">Move In Ready</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
      Construction dust gets everywhere — into cupboards, behind appliances, in air vents. Our post-renovation clean is thorough and systematic, ensuring every surface is dust-free and ready for you to move in or start using your newly renovated space.
    </p>
  </div>
</ServicePage>
